                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5496: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-06T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1924—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 6—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>325. My 318, September 2, 5 p.m., last paragraph. Naval attaché returned
                    yesterday from Harbin and Mukden, reports after careful inspection he could find
                    no evidence of Marshal Chang Tso-lin intending to move in immediate future. His
                    attitude appeared to be one of watchful waiting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
